				"speakerSlotDescription": [
					{}
				],
				"synopsis": {
					"type": 23,
					"value": "This dialogue can occur in three different states: \r\nIn the first, Inwe is in a trance, chanting a spell that will cover the druid grove in thorns. \r\nIn the second, the ritual has been stopped after a druid named Kagha was exposed as a Shadow Druid. Inwe is ashamed at her involvement.\r\nIn the third, a group of goblins that had threatened the grove has been dealt with and the grove is considered safe again. In this state, Inwe is still a bit shaken - she knows the threat is over, but she's still jumping at shadows.\r\n\r\nThe player always encounters Inwe around a sacred druid pool."
				}
			}
		}
